    "updated_at": "2016-02-26T09:23:53Z",
    "body": "Well, I'm sorry, but I do have `.desktop` files for those two applications...\n\nHere is the one for Rocket.chat (installed directly by the application in `/usr/share/applications/`:\n\n```\n[Desktop Entry]\nVersion=1.0\nType=Application\nEncoding=UTF-8\nName=Rocket.Chat\nComment=Rocket.Chat Native Cross-Platform Desktop Application via Electron.\nExec=/opt/rocketchat/rocketchat\nPath=/opt/rocketchat/\nIcon=/opt/rocketchat/icon.png\nTerminal=false\nCategories=Application;\n```\n\nAnd here is the one for Boostnote, this one I created myself, also in `/usr/share/applications/`:\n\n```\n[Desktop Entry]\nType=Application\nVersion=0.5.4\nName=Boostnote\nComment=Note-taking application for programmers\nIcon=/home/rbazile/bin/boostnote/logo.png\nExec=/home/rbazile/bin/boostnote/Boostnote\nPath=/home/rbazile/bin/boostnote\nCategories=Development;\nName[en_US]=Boostnote\n```\n\nSo yeah, I do believe it's a genuine problem (it did not happen before when I was using rocket.chat only).\n"
